; Trigonometric functions work in degrees (NC programming manual,
; "Operators and arithmetic functions"). ATAN2's angular reference is
; its second argument; the result is in degrees.
X=SIN(30) ;= 0.5
X=COS(60) ;= 0.5
X=TAN(45) ;= 1
X=ASIN(0.5) ;= 30
X=ACOS(0.5) ;= 60
X=ATAN2(30.5, 80.1) ;= 20.8455 (manual 4.1.3.1 example)
X=SQRT(POT(3)+POT(4)) ;= 5
